dical research and education as well as a strong commitment to the quality clinical care of children eight physicians and three fellows evaluate and treat children with diabetes growth disorders precocious and delayed puberty sex chromosome disorders particularly turner syndrome abnormal bone development and other hormonal problems the work done by the division successfully combines the worlds of clinical investigation and clinical care to improve the diagnosis and treatment of endocrine disorders we invite you to explore our website to learn more about who we are and what we are doing the site will continue to be updated so please check back often for recent additions fellowships we have filled our slot for july 2012 we will again use eras for our fellowship application process fellowship start date 1 july 2013 but this process has not yet started please see the details at their site we will also be part of the nrmp match if you would like to make an appointment to see a physician please contact the endocrinology or diabetes clinic clinical research basic research learn more about clinical studies we are actively involved in many clinical studies that cover a broad range of endocrine disorders our division is one of two northern california centers in a major national trial designed to identify factors predictive of insulin dependent diabetes mellitus screen families with diabetes and treat affected individuals before the development of the disease join our mailing list subscribe to the pediatric endocrinology mailing list and receive emails regarding diabetes and the pediatric diabetes program here at stanford you are here stanford medicine school of medicine departments pediatrics pediatric endocrinology navigation for this section division of pediatric endocrinology and diabetes home research faculty resources education patient care contact artificial pancreas center site navigation home research overview faculty faculty & fellows resources overview downloads use